title: hasDuplicates
description: hasDuplicates determines if the array contains any duplicate values (must be sortable values like strings or numbers)

rows: function hasDuplicates(items: T[], config: Required<HasDuplicatesConfig<T[K], K>>): boolean,

function hasDuplicates(items: T[], config: { comparator(item1: T, item2: T): number; }): boolean,
function hasDuplicates(items: T[], config?: HasDuplicatesConfig<C, K>): boolean,
function hasDuplicates(items: T[], config?: HasDuplicatesConfig<C, any>): boolean

rows.description: items array that is checked for duplicates

rows.name: config
rows.description: config to customize how items are compared to determine equality @see HasDuplicatesConfig
